Sorry, but it's not possible to revert the bytecode back to the original Solidity source code. The compilation process is a one-way function, meaning you can't reverse engineer the bytecode to get the exact Solidity code. 

This is because the Solidity compiler optimizes the code during the compilation process and all the comments, variable names, and formatting are lost. 

Although there are decompilers that can convert Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) bytecode back into a more readable format, they can't reproduce the original Solidity code. They will only provide a low-level assembly language output which is much harder to understand than Solidity.
